@host = http://localhost:3000
@baseUrl = {{host}}/api/v1
@token = Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### EMAIL-TEMPLATES MODULE - Email Marketing
### ============================================

### TEMPLATES - List Templates
GET {{baseUrl}}/email-templates?page=1&limit=20
Authorization: {{token}}

### TEMPLATES - Get Template
GET {{baseUrl}}/email-templates/:templateId
Authorization: {{token}}

### TEMPLATES - Create Template
POST {{baseUrl}}/email-templates
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Welcome Email",
  "subject": "Welcome to {{company_name}}!",
  "content": "<h1>Welcome {{user_name}}</h1><p>Thanks for joining!</p>",
  "variables": ["company_name", "user_name"]
}

### TEMPLATES - Preview Template
POST {{baseUrl}}/email-templates/preview
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "templateId": "template-uuid",
  "variables": {
    "company_name": "Acme Corp",
    "user_name": "John Doe"
  }
}

### TEMPLATES - Send Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/email-templates/send
Authorization: {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "templateId": "template-uuid",
  "to": "recipient@example.com",
  "variables": {
    "company_name": "Acme Corp",
    "user_name": "John Doe"
  }
}

### Notes:
### - All endpoints require authentication
### - Templates support Handlebars variable syntax
### - Replace UUIDs with actual IDs from your database
